# Using Microsoft 365 Copilot Pages for Collaboration

## 1. Overview

Copilot Pages provide an interactive canvas for collaboration, allowing users to:

- Convert Copilot responses into editable content
- Collaborate with others in real time
- Share and refine outputs
- Combine multiple responses into a single workspace

Pages are designed for editing, refining, and collaborating on content generated by Copilot.

---

## 2. Creating a Page

### Method 1: From Copilot Response

1. Generate a response in Copilot Chat
2. Click **Edit in Pages**
3. A new editable page is created

---

### Method 2: Add to Existing Page

- Use the dropdown next to **Edit in Pages**
- Select **Add to recent page**
- Combine multiple responses into one page

---

### Recommendation

- Review the Copilot response before converting it into a page
- Avoid directly generating pages without validation

---

## 3. Editing Pages

Users can:

- Modify text content
- Delete sections
- Add new content
- Rename the page

---

### Example

- Highlight text → Delete unwanted sections
- Rename page (e.g., "New Orleans April Trip Page")

---

## 4. Version Control

Pages support version history:

- View previous versions
- Restore earlier versions
- Track changes over time

---

## 5. Export Options

Pages can be converted into:

- Microsoft Word documents
- PowerPoint presentations
- PDF files

---

## 6. Sharing Pages

### 6.1 Share via Link

- Generate a page link
- Default: users in the organization can edit

---

### 6.2 Configure Access

Options include:

- Who can access:
  - Organization-wide
  - Specific users
- Permissions:
  - View only
  - Edit
- Expiration date for access

---

### 6.3 Share with Users

- Use **@mention**
- Select a user (e.g., Jane)
- Click **Share and Notify**

Result:
- User receives access
- Notification is sent

---

### 6.4 Embed in Apps

- Copy component
- Embed in other Microsoft 365 applications

---

## 7. Adding Content to Pages

### 7.1 Insert Options

- Hover in left margin → Click **+**
- Or press **/** (slash)

---

### 7.2 Available Components

- Tables
- Checklists
- Bulleted lists
- Numbered lists
- Dates
- Callouts
- Code blocks
- Mermaid diagrams (flowcharts)
- Math equations
- Table of contents
- Dividers
- Text styles (headings, body)
- Templates
- Communication elements
- Emoji picker
- Labels
- Images
- Planner components

---

## 8. Collaboration Features

- Multiple users can edit simultaneously
- Active editors are displayed at the top
- Real-time collaboration supported

---

## 9. Accessing Pages

Pages can be accessed via:

- **Recent Pages** (top menu)
- **Library** (left panel)
- Copilot Chat → **Recent Pages**

---

## 10. Integration with Notebooks

- Pages can be added to notebooks
- Notebook stores:
  - Page reference
  - Link to the page

---

## 11. Pages vs Notebooks

| Feature        | Pages                          | Notebooks                        |
|----------------|--------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Purpose        | Editing and collaboration      | Context aggregation              |
| Content        | Editable document              | Files and conversations          |
| Usage          | Drafting and refining          | Research and insights            |
| Collaboration  | Real-time editing              | Reference-based interaction      |

---

## 12. Best Practices

- Validate Copilot output before creating a page
- Use pages for collaborative editing
- Manage access permissions carefully
- Use version history for tracking changes
- Combine multiple responses into a single page when needed

---

## 13. Key Takeaways

- Pages are interactive and collaborative workspaces
- Allow editing and refinement of Copilot responses
- Support sharing, exporting, and embedding
- Enable real-time collaboration
- Can be integrated with notebooks for extended workflows

---
